      • getCollectionName

        public String getCollectionName()
        Description copied from interface: Feature
        A single feature descriptor can result in the generation of multiple features (e.g. in the case where it refers to a range of indexes). The collection name groups all these features under one name - that of the feature descriptor. It can used, for example, for measuring the performance of the entire collection of features together.
        Specified by:

      • addDynamicSourceCode

        public boolean addDynamicSourceCode(DynamicSourceCodeBuilder<T> builder,
                                    String variableName)
        Description copied from interface: Feature
        Add source code to a string builder, allowing us to construct this feature dynamically. To ensure that the current feature gets a value, it contain the line: 
        builder.append(variableName + " = " + ... + ";");
        Specified by:
        addDynamicSourceCode in interface Feature<T,Y>
        Parameters:
        builder - the current builder
        variableName - this feature's variable name, to which values should be assigned in the code
        Returns:
        true if this feature supports dynamic code adding, false otherwise.
